meka.classifiers.multilabel

Interface SemisupervisedClassifier

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CM, EM

    public interface SemisupervisedClassifier
    SemisupervisedClassifier.java - An Interface for Multilabel Semisupervised Classifiers. This is an interface for multi-label semisupervised classificatation. For classifiers implementing this interface, the method setUnlabelledData(unlabeledInstances) will be called prior to buildClassifier(trainingInstances). Note that as of writing this comment, this is only the test data -- there is not yet any option for setting other unlabelled data -- although this is planned for future versions.
    Version:
    January 2012
    Author:
    Jesse Read (jesse@tsc.uc3m.es)
